<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-551-842  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 551 842.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Sept 1989 v2 n9 p68(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A software Sherlock for hardware hassles. (Software Review) (DTGInc System Sleuth)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Holtzman, Jeff.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   DTG Inc. (products).andO;Product:   System Sleuth (Performance analysis software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Utility ProgramsEvaluationDiagnostics.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Who knows what evil lurks in the heart of your PC-what conflicts amongterminate-and-stayresident programs, what struggles among add-in cards andsoftware to control certain key interrupts?andM;System Sleuth knows.andP;  System Sleuth is a diagnostic program that peers intothe innards of a PC and provides information on half a dozen topics,including system configuration, memory usage, and disk format.andP;  Theinformation it provides is not all that hard to come by, but you'd need TheNorton Utilities, several other programs, and a couple of technical referencemanuals to duplicate what System Sleuth conveniently provides all in onepackage.andM;System Sleuth reveals general system information (such as processor type,BIOS date, DOS version, and number of ports and their hardware addresses),hard disk format information, and displays that help resolve conflicts amongTSRs or add-in cards.andM;The program has its faults; sometimes it incorrectly identifies hardware orsoftware items.andP;  For example, System Sleuth reported that a multiusermultitasking operating system (PCMOS/386) was active on one test machine-aToshiba T1000 one of the smallest laptops.andM;Even so, System Sleuth is useful if you're trying to learn more about your PCand as a tool for resolving hardware and software conflicts and learningabout such DOS mysteries as device drivers and interrupts.andP;  That informationwon't make a systems progammer out of you, but it is a painless way to learnabout what's going on under your PC's hood.andM;System Sleuth costs $149.andP;  Contact DTG, Inc., in El Toro, California, at800-999-1557 or 714-5872226.andO;</TEXT></DOC>